ol.li:
Change the synopsis of the primary template definition of default_delete in [unique.ptr.dltr.dflt] as indicated:

namespace std {
  template <class T> struct default_delete {
    constexpr default_delete() = default;
    template <class U> default_delete(const default_delete<U>&);
    void operator()(T*) const;
  };
}

Remove the prototype specification of the default_delete default constructor in [unique.ptr.dltr.dflt]/1. This brings it in harmony with the style used in the partial specialization default_delete<T[]>. Since there are neither implied nor explicit members, there is no possibility to misinterpret what the constructor does:
constexpr default_delete();
1 Effects: Default constructs a default_delete object.

Change the synopsis of the partial specialization of default_delete in [unique.ptr.dltr.dflt1] as indicated:

namespace std {
  template <class T> struct default_delete<T[]> {
    constexpr default_delete() = default;
    void operator()(T*) const;
    template <class U> void operator()(U*) const = delete;
  };
}
